Gold One, JD Group, Netcare, Vodacom May Move: South Africa Stock Preview

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-05-15T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/gold-one-jd-group-netcare-vodacom-south-africa-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 278.10,
or 0.9 percent, to 31,959.93 in Johannesburg.  Gold One International Ltd. (GDO)  : The gold producer is
scheduled to release an announcement about a takeover. Gold One
shares halted trading on May 13 at 3.35 rand.  JD Group Ltd. (JDG SJ): The furniture and appliance
retailer releases first-half earnings. The shares gained 9
cents, or 0.2 percent, to 46.30 rand.  Netcare Ltd. (NTC)  : South Africa’s largest private-
hospital operator, publishes first-half results. Netcare dropped
3 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 14.02 rand.  Vodacom Group Ltd. (VOD)  : The largest provider of
mobile-phone services announces full-year earnings. Vodacom
climbed 90 cents, or 1.1 percent, to 79.90 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY)   fell 1.9 percent to $23.48.
 AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU)   dropped 1.9 percent to $43.61.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) declined 1.8 percent to $75.76.
 DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY)   slid 2.6 percent to $4.91. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) slipped 1.3 percent to $15.34. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) dropped 2.3 percent to $13.13. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) fell 2.7 percent to $26.18.  Sappi Ltd. (SPP)   dropped 2 percent to $5.04.  Sasol Ltd. (SSL)   declined 1.7
percent to $51.20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
